[h2][b]Usage[/b][/h2]

[h2]Enabling data collection[/h2]

Data collection is [b]disabled by default[/b]. Open [b]Options Menu > Extension Options > Station Ware History[/b] and enable [b]Enable Data Collection[/b] to start sampling. Adjust [b]Collection Interval[/b] (1-10 minutes) and [b]Retention Period[/b] (10-120 hours) as needed.

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-StationWareHistory/refs/heads/main/docs/images/extension_options.png[/img]

[h2]Graph Limitations[/h2]

Due to engine limitations on total data points, graph capacity depends on your display settings:
[list]
[*] Absolute Maximum: Up to 8 wares simultaneously under ideal conditions.
[*] Standard Limit: No more than 5 wares under normal use.
[*] "Both" Mode: Limited to 2 wares (since this mode doubles the lines per ware).
[/list]
When the limit ill be reached, checkboxes for additional wares will be disabled.

[h2]Opening the history graph[/h2]
[list]
[*] Right-click any player-owned station and choose [b]Show Ware History[/b] from the interaction menu.
[/list]
  [img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-StationWareHistory/refs/heads/main/docs/images/interaction_menu.png[/img]
[list]
[*] Or open any of that station's menus ([b]Station configuration[/b], [b]Logical station overview[/b], [b]Transaction Log[/b]) and click the **Station
[/list]
  [img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-StationWareHistory/refs/heads/main/docs/images/station_menus_right_bar.png[/img]

[h2]The graph menu[/h2]
[list]
[*] [b]Station[/b]: Switch between any player-owned station with recorded history without closing the menu. Display mode and zoom carry over to the new station (re-clamped to its own data range); selected wares are kept only where they also exist on the new station.
[*] [b]Display[/b]: Choose [b]Real Amount[/b], [b]With Reservations[/b], or [b]Both[/b].
[list]
[*] [b]With Reservations[/b] is a default option that shows the stock amount as it should be once all pending trades are executed.
[*] [b]Both[/b] is unavailable once 3 or more wares are checked.
[/list]
[/list]
  [img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-StationWareHistory/refs/heads/main/docs/images/selection_value_types.png[/img]
[list]
[*] [b]Wares[/b]: Check up to 8 wares (4 in "Both" mode) to plot. Each gets its own colour, assigned in the order you check them and remembered across reopens.
[*] [b]Show Less / Show More[/b]: Shrink or widen the visible time window. "Show More" disables once the window already covers the station's full recorded history.
[/list]
